17_23	0.093404645	Whether their forecast was a true prediction or just a lucky guess, it reinforces Dieterich's confidence in an emerging paradigm of earthquake science: the importance of crustal stress changes in triggering or inhibiting future quakes.
17_24	0.10822802	In recent years, quake specialists have developed computer models to understand how quakes change the stress on Earth's crust.
17_25	0.10076226	Some research suggests that past California quakes have been either triggered or inhibited by stress changes induced by quakes elsewhere.
